From: Pei Li <peili.dev@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 25 Jun 2024 09:42:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] jfs: Fix shift-out-of-bounds in dbDiscardAG
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.6.47
Git-commit: 7063b80268e2593e58bee8a8d709c2f3ff93e2f2

[ Upstream commit 7063b80268e2593e58bee8a8d709c2f3ff93e2f2 ]

When searching for the next smaller log2 block, BLKSTOL2() returned 0,
causing shift exponent -1 to be negative.

This patch fixes the issue by exiting the loop directly when negative
shift is found.

Reported-by: syzbot+61be3359d2ee3467e7e4@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Closes: https://syzkaller.appspot.com/bug?extid=61be3359d2ee3467e7e4
Signed-off-by: Pei Li <peili.dev@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Kleikamp <dave.kleikamp@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 fs/jfs/jfs_dmap.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/jfs/jfs_dmap.c b/fs/jfs/jfs_dmap.c
index 8eec84c651bf..19eddbc5d616 100644
--- a/fs/jfs/jfs_dmap.c
+++ b/fs/jfs/jfs_dmap.c
@@ -1626,6 +1626,8 @@ s64 dbDiscardAG(struct inode *ip, int agno, s64 minlen)
 		} else if (rc == -ENOSPC) {
 			/* search for next smaller log2 block */
 			l2nb = BLKSTOL2(nblocks) - 1;
+			if (unlikely(l2nb < 0))
+				break;
 			nblocks = 1LL << l2nb;
 		} else {
 			/* Trim any already allocated blocks */
